Description: Fragment of conical foot of large Chian pottery open vessel; exterior slipped white and reserved with traces of decoration; two brown lines and a band at edge of foot; outside of foot glazed; white band around edge of otherwise reserved underside; inscription on underside.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GD.2199) (phase 2)
